On this episode of the Major Issues Podcast, we journey into Wakanda as Bryan Edward Hill and Stefano Caselli reimagine the Black Panther mythos for Marvel’s new Ultimate Universe! Ultimate Black Panther gives us a T’Challa who must balance tradition, isolation, and a looming war with Moon Knight’s brutal forces across Africa. We break down the bold themes, striking visuals, and character choices that set this series apart. How does Hill’s approach reshape T’Challa’s responsibilities as king and hero? What makes this version of Wakanda feel so alive and dangerous? We dive deep into every powerful moment—whether you’re a longtime Black Panther fan or just stepping into the Ultimate line, this discussion is for you!

Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

